FT  24 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Hobson has 53% take-up of shares
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BLACKWELL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Hobson, the vehicle for 28-year-old Mr Andrew Regan, yesterday reported the
take-up of 52.7 per cent of the shares available in last month's public and
open offer.
Shareholders yesterday also gave the go-ahead at an extraordinary general
meeting for the company's plan to buy the food manufacturing division of
Co-operative Wholesale Society Limited for Pounds 111m.
Swiss Bank Corporation, which fully placed shares worth Pounds 26.6m with
institutions on April 28, underwrote the public offer.
Mr Regan became chief executive after reversing Cadismark, his household
products business, into Hobson at the end of 1992. The shares, traded on the
USM, were suspended on February 10 at 27p pending the announcement of the
CWS deal. The acquisition is expected to be completed on Friday when
dealings in the new shares are expected to begin.
