FT  24 MAY 94 / Letters to the Editor: Pensions ingenuity already displayed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr PHILIP WARLAND
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, It does not require, as you state in your leading article, 'Revisionism
on pensions' (May 17), ingenuity from the City 'to reduce the capital market
threat to the value of the (defined contribution) pension on the date of
retirement'.
That ingenuity has already been displayed by the production of equity-based
annuities. What is required is a swift decision by the Inland Revenue to
allow pensioners to benefit immediately.
In the longer term the requirement to liquidate a personal pension and buy
an annuity should be removed and replaced by simple rules on the withdrawal
of income and capital from the fund.
Philip Warland,
