<HEADLINE>
FT  23 MAY 94 / International Company News: Alcan Aluminium buys sheet maker
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Alcan Aluminium has bought Leichtmetallwerk Nachterstedt, an aluminium sheet
business in former East Germany, from the Treuhandanstalt for an undisclosed
sum, writes Robert Gibbens in Montreal.
The plant will be restructured to make automotive sheet and building and
industrial sheet products.
It will become a finishing plant for Alcan's joint venture rolling mills in
West Germany and will serve emerging east European markets, Alcan said.
