FT  23 MAY 94 / Arts (Openings): War Artists
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Imperial War Museum opens two new displays on Wednesday, 'The Slade
School' display shows the work of commissioned war artists in the later
years of the First World War: Lewis, Nash, Bomberg, Nevinson, Spencer,
Wadsworth and others. 'Europe Regained' follows artists including Ardizzone,
Bawden, Gross and Weight through campaigns in Italy, France and Germany,
after 1943.
