FT  23 MAY 94 / Customs may take VAT case to Lords
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Customs and Excise is likely to appeal to the Lords after losing a case in
which it claimed value added tax worth Pounds 9.5m from a mail order company
selling through agents.
Three Court of Appeal judges ruled by a two-to-one majority that agents of
Bradford-based Fine Art Developments did not have to declare for VAT
purposes what they had sold.
Customs and Excise said the case revolved around the fact that VAT was only
being paid by agents on the price of the goods sold to them. It was not paid
on the full selling price to customers.
